  <front>
   <head>The EXCEPTION.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">has gain'd one branch of fame,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">To which, I'll prove, he has no claim.</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Say they â€” "His favours he extends,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">"Without regard to wealth, or friends:</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">"Of such disinterested spirit,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">"Nothing prevails, with him, but merit;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">"Nay, he'll dispense with merit too,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">"When modest want can reach his view. "</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Mere prejudice! 'tis plain to me,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">No man takes sweeter bribes than he.</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">To clear this point from any doubt,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">A parallel shall help me out.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The noble FULVIA spurns at gain:</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Freely she heals her lover's pain:</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But, surely, you'll allow me this,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">That when she grants, she shares the bliss.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">So STANHOPE, in each gen'rous action,</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Reaps more than half the satisfaction.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
